regulator, a study sponsored by the Corporation of London has concluded.
In the aftermath of the collapse of Taurus, the Stock Exchange settlement
system, the Bank has proposed a successor system, to be known as Crest,
which it said it or a commercial vendor might operate.
The report notes that in other centres, responsibility for equity settlement
tends to be shared between the stock exchange, banks and brokers.
