FT  10 SEP 93 / Airline launches season ticket
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL BETTS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH MIDLAND Airways, the UK independent airline, is to launch a season
ticket fare which it claims will save between 37 per cent and 65 per cent
for business travellers on busy European routes, Paul Betts writes.
The scheme, Diamond EuroPass, will entitle business travellers to five fully
flexible return business-class journeys to be made on any of its direct
international routes within three months of purchase.
The pass will be priced in two bands: Pounds 799 covering travel between
London Heathrow and Amsterdam, Brussels, Paris and Dublin; and Pounds 999
for travel on any route on the airline's international network. It will be
available from September 13 in the UK and the end of the month overseas.
