<HEADLINE>
FT  10 SEP 93 / League table for Names' agents
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SHARP DIFFERENCES in the performances of members' agencies at the Lloyd's
insurance market are disclosed in a survey published yesterday by the
Association of Lloyd's Members, the organisation which represents more than
9,000 Names. Members agents handle the affairs of Names whose assets support
Lloyd's.
Two small agencies - Hardy and Gravett &amp; Tilling - come top of the ALM
league table, producing average pre-tax profits (before Lloyd's and agency
charges) of 9.8 per cent and 8 per cent (of gross capacity or allowable
premium income) respectively in the five years 1986 to 1990.
The best performing larger agencies were Kiln, Roberts &amp; Hiscox and Murray
Lawrence, which produced average returns for Names of 5.2 per cent, 4.8 per
cent and 4.4 per cent in the same five years.
Some 65 agencies are currently active in the Lloyd's market compared to 250
in 1984.
