<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 93 / World Stock Markets: Foreign demand fuels Brazil
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRAZILIAN equities showed fresh strength at midsession in response to
foreign demand, but lost some ground later on moderate profit-taking.
The Bovespa index was finally a net 133, or 1.1 per cent, ahead at 11,751,
after touching 12,236.
Equities have been attracting interest after the government announced its
intention to tackle inflation, currently at a monthly level of 34 per cent,
by adopting fiscal reform measures and accelerating the privatisation
programme.
BUENOS AIRES reversed a fresh retreat on profit-taking to close higher on
the day in response to late news of the approval by key Senate committees of
a draft for a pensions reform bill.
The weighted Merval index, which initially lost 3 per cent, finished a net 1
per cent up at 482.60.
