FT  09 SEP 93 / International Company News: Dr Pepper 'poison pill' suit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A SHAREHOLDER of Dr Pepper/Seven-Up has filed a suit against the company and
its directors in Delaware Chancery Court alleging they have breached their
fiduciary duties by thwarting a possible bid for the company's shares,
Reuter reports.
Dr Pepper recently adopted a 'poison pill' defence against a possible
hostile takeover attempt by Cadbury Schweppes, the UK confectionery and soft
drinks group.
In August, Cadbury said it was buying a 20.2 per cent stake in Dr Pepper. It
has not ruled out a bid sometime in the future.
Dr Pepper said its board adopted a shareholder rights plan aimed at assuring
holders are treated fairly should a takeover become imminent.
The company said the plan was not intended to prevent a takeover on terms
beneficial to shareholders.
The Delaware suit was filed last Friday and made public yesterday. It asked
the court for a preliminary injunction as soon as possible.
