<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Phoenix Timber gives details of Pounds 3m
refinancing plan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Phoenix Timber fell 1 1/2 p to 12 1/2 p after announcing further
details of its refinancing under which it is raising Pounds 2.94m to cut
borrowings.
The Co-operation Retirement Benefit Fund has already subscribed Pounds 1.44m
in Pounds 1 loans at par. These are now being offered to existing
shareholders on the basis of Pounds 1 nominal for 10 shares held at a price
of 111p each.
Some Pounds 1.5m is being raised by a rights issue of 5-for-8 and 125 for
Pounds 16 nominal loan notes at 8p per share. The issue is underwritten by
CRBF.
At the same time the 25p shares are being split into 5p ordinary and 20p
deferred which are considered valueless.
As a result of the moves CRBF may end up with more than 30 per cent but the
Takeover Panel has waived the need to make a full offer. Mr John Bushell, Mr
Charles Benham and Mr Robert Ainsworth are leaving the board. Mr Duncan
Saville, who is a director of CRBF, and Mr Lars Ahrell are to become
directors.
CRBF said that it considered its investment to be long term and it intends
to maintain the listing.
</TEXT>
