<TEXT>
Sir, Joe Rogaly, in his article, 'Marx the musical' (September 7), doubted
whether any of his readers would be able to whistle the tune to the chorus
beginning 'Strong as the steel which we shape with precision'.
I cannot whistle but I suggest singing it (in the bath in my case) to the
tune Epiphany Hymn, used for 'Brightest and best of the sons of the
morning'. I think it sounds very good.
My wife would disagree.
Andrew G Gibbs,
