FT  09 SEP 93 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
We are assured that ITV's substitute for 'This Week', the half-hour current
affairs programme The Big Story, which is launched today at 7.30, will be
hard hitting, popular, and 'searching out the often shocking truth hidden
behind the headlines'.
Thanks to the character of Victor Meldrew, 'One Foot In The Grave' has
attracted more attention than the other oldie comedy, Waiting For God, which
begins a fresh batch on BBC1. Yet Waiting For God seems to me the better
series, particularly strong on dialogue and in the superb acting partnership
between Stephanie Cole and Graham Crowden (8.30).
Crimewatch UK is back with a mouth-watering menu. There's a reconstruction
of the last day in the lives of a 64-year-old man and his 67-year-old wife
who were shot dead in their Welsh farmhouse (sounds super]) a young woman
telling us all about how she was raped (yummy yummy]) and reports of a woman
being spied on as she changed after a game of squash (cor]). Drooling over
this is quite OK because it's all in the name of crime prevention (9.30).
</TEXT>
